<article id="post-1435" class="post-1435 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-rants category-technology tag-analysis tag-management tag-problem-solving tag-programming">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2009/07/i-wouldnt-have-done-it-that-way/" rel="bookmark">I wouldn&#039;t have done it that way</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>I&#8217;ve recently run into a common programming problem. While turning a development project over to another development agency, we heard that worst of comments:</p>
<blockquote><p>Why did you build it that way?</p></blockquote>
<p>It seems like a simple question. <strong>But it belies it&#8217;s true meaning.</strong> What they&#8217;re really saying is:</p>
<blockquote><p>We wouldn&#8217;t have done that. This design is bad.</p></blockquote>
<p>It&#8217;s a completely valid point. And you know what? <strong>I probably already thought that same thing.</strong><br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2009/07/i-wouldnt-have-done-it-that-way/#more-1435" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;I wouldn&#039;t have done it that way&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2009/07/i-wouldnt-have-done-it-that-way/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2009-07-03T10:29:49-06:00">3 July 2009</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/rants/" rel="category tag">Rants</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/technology/" rel="category tag">Technology</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/analysis/" rel="tag">analysis</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/management/" rel="tag">management</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/problem-solving/" rel="tag">problem solving</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/programming/" rel="tag">programming</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2009/07/i-wouldnt-have-done-it-that-way/#comments">1 Comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on I wouldn&#039;t have done it that way</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
