<article id="post-964" class="post-964 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-careers category-costa-rica category-general category-technology tag-critical-mass tag-management tag-rolex">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/05/what-have-you-done-with-spocks-brain/" rel="bookmark">What have you done with Spock&#039;s brain?</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>One of the hard parts about leaving any group is passing your legacy off to someone else. It doesn&#8217;t matter if it&#8217;s a short-term thing (e.g. vacation) or a long-term thing (e.g. leaving the company). It still has to happen &#8212; unless you&#8217;re a total jerk and want to leave people hanging, that is. It&#8217;s just how you carry it out.<br />
I&#8217;m on my second round of brain transfer in two months. The first time was when I was getting ready to go on vacation. I had to pass off my daily tasks to someone else so they&#8217;d get done. But you can&#8217;t easily toss one person&#8217;s work onto just one other person. Especially when you know there&#8217;s a lot to be done. A month ago, I used four people.<br />
This time, it&#8217;s just one. My replacement.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/05/what-have-you-done-with-spocks-brain/#more-964" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;What have you done with Spock&#039;s brain?&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/05/what-have-you-done-with-spocks-brain/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2008-05-07T16:56:08-06:00">7 May 2008</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/careers/" rel="category tag">Careers</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/costa-rica/" rel="category tag">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/technology/" rel="category tag">Technology</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/critical-mass/" rel="tag">critical mass</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/management/" rel="tag">management</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/rolex/" rel="tag">rolex</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/05/what-have-you-done-with-spocks-brain/#respond">Leave a comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on What have you done with Spock&#039;s brain?</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
